<P>THE CHURCHES Shall Know that CHRIST Searcheth the Hearts. Set forth in The <HI>fir&s;t SERMON</HI> that was preach'd in the <HI>New Meeting-Hou&s;e</HI> in <HI>Summer-&s;treet, Bo&s;ton.</HI> On <HI>January</HI> 8. 1716, 17. being a day of <HI>Fa&s;ting and Prayer;</HI> to ob|tain Gods gracious pre&s;ence with, and Ble&s;&s;ing on, the <HI>Congregation</HI> who de&s;ign'd to attend Gods publick Wor&s;hip in that Place; and now publi&s;h'd at their de&s;ire.</P>
<P>By <HI>Benjamin Wad&s;worth,</HI> A. M. Pa&s;|tor of a Church of Chri&s;t in <HI>Bo&s;|ton, N. E.</HI></P>
<Q><BIBL>Prov. 15. 3.</BIBL>
<HI>The Eyes of the Lord are in eve|ry place, beholding the evil and the good.</HI></Q>
